params.owner: The owner address of this contract

returns.answer: The answer for the latest round: 0 if the sequencer is up, 1 if it is down.
returns.answeredInRound: The round ID of the round in which the answer was computed.
returns.roundId: The round ID from the aggregator for which the data was retrieved combined with a phase to ensure that round IDs get larger as time moves forward.
returns.startedAt: The timestamp when the round was started.
returns.updatedAt: The timestamp of the block in which the answer was updated on L1.

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

params.isDown: True if the sequencer is down, false otherwise
params.timestamp: The timestamp when the sequencer changed status

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

latestRoundData().notice: Returns the health status of the sequencer.

setAnswer(bool,uint256).notice: Updates the health status of the sequencer.
